      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease and line a 900 g loaf tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix wet ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mash the {{bananas}} thoroughly in a large bowl until almost smooth, a few lumps are fine. Stir in the {{light-brown-sugar}}, {{vegetable-oil}}, and {{vanilla-extract}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add dry ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{ground-cinnamon}}. Stir until just combined, do not overmix. Fold in the {{walnuts}} if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 50 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the batter into the tin. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The top will crack along the centre as it bakes. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes before turning out.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
